## Behavior

After completing code changes to any file listed above:

1. Read the dependency map to identify which design docs may be affected
2. Skim the relevant sections (not the whole doc) to check if descriptions still match the code
3. If a mismatch is found, update the design doc section to match the new code
4. Report what was checked and what (if anything) was updated

## Principle

Design docs are the authority for understanding system architecture. Code expresses behavior but not intent, trade-offs, or degradation strategies. If someone reads only the design doc, they should get an accurate picture of how the system works — without needing to read the code.

## What This Rule Does NOT Cover

- Adding new design docs (covered by component-lifecycle-gate pattern)
- Cursor rule sync (each .mdc manages its own scope)
- API docs (`docs/API.md`) — maintained separately
